:INFO
The Novel That Made My Apartment Feel Inhabited
I started The Haunting of Hill House at 10pm on a Thursday because I thought \
two chapters before bed would be fine. It was not fine. Shirley Jackson's novel \
operates through the slow accumulation of wrongness: architecture that does not \
follow the rules of architecture, angles that are not quite right, a narrator \
whose perception you stop being able to trust. By midnight I was not enjoying \
the book. I was enduring it and I could not stop.

:NOW
Wondering if Eleanor was ever safe from the beginning

:QUOTE [subtitle:Shirley Jackson, quotetype:PLAIN]
Hill House, not sane, stood by itself against its hills, holding darkness within.

:JOURNEY
Reading Hill House
Section
Tension
- Opening prose | 5 | Perfect construction
- The house | 5 | Unmatched wrongness
- Eleanor's unraveling | 5 | Precise and unsettling
- The ending | 5 | Completely earned | One of the only horror endings that fully lands

:NOW
Thinking about rereading The Haunting of Hill House during the day to see whether \
the experience is different in the light.

